Name: 36_learning_brain_think_model
Representative_Docs:
['@Miles_Brundage people also got overly optimistic about chatbots. and not every expert thought that closed-domain games were a measure of very much. as i have been saying since 2012, the real challenge for deep learning is reasoning, generalization and comprehension. 

that remains true.', 'If Biden can be president, so can a large language model.', "Lack of access to large language models is one of those problems that Moore's law will solve while we're busy thinking about it.", '@McAllesterDavid @ilyasut @jurafsky @manning @percyliang Our main argument in favor of the grounding hypothesis is that the structure of the world is way too rich and complex to be expressed by humans in linguistic form. Hence learning from pure human-produced text cannot possibly lead a machine to a deep understanding of the world.', '@IntuitMachine No, different tools are better for different things, and deep learning is only best for some things.', "At the current rate, we're less than a year away from having models with more connections than the human brain.", '@yudapearl @ylecun @aminkarbasi @AlexTensor @KordingLab @GaryMarcus Inductive bias is any knowledge or assumptions that you have prior to seeing the data. It includes choice of model class, Bayesian priors, and - most relevant here - anything you care to state in a formal language like logic. The whole field of ILP is about the latter. (1/2)', "Neural nets that analyze/generate text, speech, image, proteins don't tell us much about the structure thereof.
But
1. they are very useful
2. they tell us that SGD is better at structure discovery than humans
3. they upset people who devoted their career to structure discovery", 'A good example of what I mean when I refer to large language models (LLMs) as "alien artifacts". Obviously powerful, especially if you poke it just right.', "Experience consistently shows that the same results can be obtained with many different learning algorithms. Transformers or deep learning are almost certainly not the only (or best) way to build chat models. It's time to explore."]

Name: 74_customers_customer_cx_customerexperience
Representative_Docs:
["More things that *haven't* changed about customer experience. Good adds via @AshokNellikar.  #CX #CustomerExperience", 'Adapting to customer preferences is about giving the customer what they want, the way they want it, and being easy to do business with. And, that has everything to do with creating ‚ÄúCustomer Amazement.‚Äù', 'Want more #customers? Ease and simplicity are table stakes. 

Simplify your app, #website, the buying process, your return #policies, customer instructions, and access to customer support.

Customers‚Äô lives are complicated. That‚Äôs why ease rules. #customerexperience #cx #custserv', 'Customer service gives you the competitive edge. It‚Äôs that simple. For the right level of customer service, some customers will drive further, wait longer & even be willing to spend more money to get a better level of service.', '#CXQOTD Customers THINK about the product, but they FEEL the experience. Great service, not product, is about emotional connection 
QUI QUOTE: The more emotional the connection, the more memorable the experience, the more loyal the customer
#customerservice #custserv #custexp #cx', "A4 | #custserv

If your customer service is truly awesome, you won't need to spend a dime marketing it at all. Your customers will do it for you. Other customers will trust that over what you say about yourself.", 'Your advertising online is not your New Marketing. It‚Äôs your customers raving about you on social media. Make sure you have them tell a great story about your exceptional customer service.
#CustomerService #CustomerExperience #custserv #custexp #cx', '"You're always selling something." 

Great advice from an old mentor.

In #CX that means you're always building the case for customers. Sometimes over and over again. 

Keep going. Most people want to do right by customers, too. Show them some ways to do it 

#CustomerExperience', 'When you‚Äôre trying to get your customers to buy into the #CX you‚Äôre creating for them, it‚Äôs the story that will do it. Create an image in your customer‚Äôs mind. If you really want to get them excited, get your customers to help paint that picture in the form of online reviews.', 'Your brand is not the result of your #marketing actions. Your brand is the perception your customers have of your customer service actions.
#CustomerService #CustomerExperience #custserv #custexp #cx']

Name: 80_customer_cx_customerexperience_employees
Representative_Docs:
['Treat employees like you want the customer treated ‚Äì maybe even better. It starts at the top. Be an example of the behavior you want employees to exhibit to their customers & their fellow employees.', 'Customer service experience is the part of the customer experience when the customer requires help or service. https://t.co/SE9XBOwY5w #customerexperience #customerservice', 'You must create the right employee experience that is motivating and fulfilling if you want to have a chance at creating the right customer experience.

Here are ten ways to motivate your employees and improve the CX.

https://t.co/TJ8jmJMHOA #customerservice #customerexperience', 'My pleasure, @collins_cla. I appreciate you.
Focus as much on creating a great employee experience
as you do the customer experience and you will earn the loyalty of both.
#EmployeeExperience #CustomerExperience #custexp #cx', "My belief is that customer service is not a department‚Äîit's a philosophy that is part of an organization's culture and is everyone's responsibility. Every employee has an impact on the customer service and the customer experience an organization provides.", 'QUI #CUSTOMEREXPERIENCE STRATEGY via @StevenVBe: Empower employees to choose for the customer
Now, this last one is crucial. If you really want to have a great impact in #CX, make sure that your frontline staff is empowered to take decisions on their own in favor of the customer.', 'For business success, think BIG, act small. Treat each customer like they are your only customer. #custserv', 'Care exceptionally for your employees and they will care exceptionally for your customers. When U create a great experience for your employees as much as U do for your customers, U will earn the loyalty of both
#EmployeeExperience #custserv #custexp #cx
@collins_cla @ddu17 @Hyken', 'What do customers want? Simply, customers want a good experience, & customer service plays a big part in that. It‚Äôs more than just the front line interacting with customers. Every employee has an impact on the customer service & the customer experience an organization provides.', "Companies survey customers much more often than they do their employees. What's wrong with that picture? 
If you keep employees happy, they will keep the customers happy? But you need to find out how they feel. #CXChat #EmployeeExperience"]

Representative_Docs: ['Thread. Great opportunity for undergraduates in computer science!', 'Interesting study', '@stacysherman @CXupdate Excellent book.  For me it was "The Little Prince". There is a specific chapter I reread before significant events. Literature transforms and transports us to new places and thoughts.  Fantastic!', '@Emil_Mauritzson You‚Äôre kind. And books are great. Would recommend books.', "At the end of my PhD, I wish I had taken the time to write out a 5 year research plan. Being able to go from paper ideas to a research program (micro to macro) is really valuable in academia and industry and we really don't get that much practice", 'On April 6, my new book, The God Equation: the Quest for a Theory of Everything, hits the bookstores. I will be on a national (on-line) book tour, speaking of the greatest quest in the history of science, the search for a single equation to unify all the laws of the universe.', 'This is my 500-page book, published by Oxford University Press: "Archimedes to Hawking: Laws of Science and the Great Minds Behind Them." Martin Gardner wrote of the book: "Clifford Pickover has brilliantly succeeded in a monumental task." https://t.co/ART7gpKloN', 'Another book to put on the list to read!', 'Amazing - I love science üòçüëçüèª', 'Time travel. Hyperspace. Star ships. Alien civilizations. Parallel universes. The Multiverse. These are the topics I cover in my course, Physics 332: The Physics of Science Fiction. (It starts Aug. 26, so there is time to register. But sorry, it is for CCNY students only.)']
